overview: The user initiated a task to enhance a sleep questionnaire application
  by adding database functionality, an admin dashboard, and an authentication
  system. After an initial codebase evaluation, a plan was developed to
  integrate a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) for storing questionnaire responses,
  implement API endpoints for data management and CSV export, and build a simple
  admin dashboard. A key decision involved simplifying the authentication system
  from a custom HMAC-signed session to a more streamlined Next.js
  middleware-based approach with a basic cookie, improving code cleanliness and
  leveraging Next.js features. The implementation covered updating demographic
  fields, creating a Prisma schema, developing API routes, and building the
  dashboard UI. The conversation concluded with setting up environment
  variables, running database migrations, and preparing for comprehensive
  testing of the new features.
